               <head>Sermons of the Ghaus-i A'zam, 'Abdulqadir Jilani</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Jāmiʿ al-favāʾid</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2006003807 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010109193" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_976-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21807">Jāmiʿ al-favāʾid</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21807">جامع الفوائد</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Rare copy of an anonymous Persian translation of the collection of sermons entitled <title>Jāmiʿ al-favāʾid</title> delivered to his disciples by <persName key="person_71359982" role="ant">Shaykh ʿAbd al-Qādir al-Jīlānī</persName> (d. 561/1166) and edited by his son, <persName key="person_f7570" role="edt">Sharaf al-Dīn ʿĪsá</persName>.
                        </p>
                        <p>The translation was intended as a study aid for students. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 608v): completed by <persName key="person_f7112" role="scr">Fakhr al-Dīn Ḥasanī al-Jīlānī</persName> on Monday, 27 Rabīʿ II 1147/26 September 1734. 

                        </p>
                        <p>The work is followed on the last leaf (f. 609) by a brief unrelated text on the <persName>
                              <persName key="person_97245226" role="subject">Prophet Muḥammad</persName>
                           </persName>. This is accompanied in a different hand (upper right corner) with a detailed description of the manuscript’s specific features with raqm annotations (foliation, verses, rubrication, binding, scribe’s compensation and grant, collator’s compensation, and total valuation).
 
                        </p>
                        <p>Second folio (beginning of text) may be a replacement; folios damaged by wormholes and water stains; repaired with net overlay; rebound in a red India Office Library binding. 
</p>
                        <p>Seal impressions (f. 1r): (circular seal) <persName key="person_f7483" role="asn">Qāz̤ī Riz̤āʾ khādim-i sharīʿat-i ʿizz-i Muḥammad</persName> (?) year 17; (rectangular seal) <persName key="person_f7649" role="asn">Z̤iyāʾ al-Dīn</persName> 1165; (rectangular seal) <persName key="person_f7294" role="asn">Mīr Muḥammad Bakhsh</persName> 1717; (rectangular seal) bandah-'i dargāh <persName key="person_f7174" role="asn">ʿIbād Allāh</persName> [regnal year] 14, 1186; (square seal) <persName key="person_f7210" role="asn">Kāmgār Khān</persName>; (square seal) <persName key="person_f7388" role="asn">Muḥammad Naṣr ʿAlī Khān</persName> 1220. 

                        </p>
                     </note>
